job_description:
Day-to-day your responsibilities will extend to:
Directly participating in the production and proofing of data operations deliverables;
Data processing, including re-coding and weighting data, running cross-tabs and creating charts;
Juggling a fluid schedule; prioritising and re-prioritising tasks within an evolving workload;
Taking ownership of medium complexity projects with responsibility for delivery of research data;
Assisting in managing client relationships as and when required with a focus on improving quality, efficiency and profitability;
Advising clients on requirements, analysis and statistical methods; in person and by email/phone;
Handling multiple concurrent projects, ensuring deadlines are met and quality controls are upheld;
Utlising bespoke technology to visualise data outputs and QAing data outputs;
Assisting colleagues when workloads require and embracing Savantas brand values.
About You
With exposure to all core functions across a fast paced, growing business, this role is ideally suited to someone with a good knowledge of the market research operations looking to expand their knowledge and skill set to advance their career at pace.
The successful applicant will also demonstrate:
A minimum of 2 years relevant and comparable experience working with data;
Knowledge of survey design, data modelling and analysis, production of visuals and presentations;
Proven ability to prioritise with a track record of meeting deadlines and working to time constraints;
Advanced English language communication skills - both verbal and written;
Ability to adapt and remain focused in a dynamic, fast-paced and growing business;
Exceptional attention to detail with an analytical problem-solving mindset;
Experience of using a statistical package such as SPSS and/or Q Pro (advantageous);
Advanced knowledge of MS Excel with VBA macro writing (advantageous);
Programming knowledge in a major programming language (advantageous).
